Formatting Functions

Data Cloud provides several formatting SQL functions to use with calculated insights.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Rtrim Function

rtrim(str)—Removes the trailing space characters from str.

Arguments

str—A string expression.
trimStr—The string characters to trim. The default is a single space.
Substring Function

substr(str, pos[, len])—Returns the substring of str that starts at pos and is of length len, or returns the slice of byte array that starts at pos and is of length len.

SELECT COUNT(SUBSTRING(ssot__Account__dlm.ssot__AccountTypeId__c, 1, 9)) AS count_of_account_type__c, ssot__Account__dlm.ssot__Id__c AS account_id__c FROM ssot__Account__dlm GROUP BY account_id__c
